The paper focuses on using machine learning to understand social situations depicted in movie clips, which involves analyzing visual and textual information. Therefore, computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) are likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques to build socially intelligent robots. Finally, the paper also mentions the grounding of interactions and attributes in the video, which suggests a potential connection to multimedia (cs.MM).
